Level 56+ Magician - League of Levity<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utibben00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tibben00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/22/02 1:47:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My 2cp</span><hr size=1> &quot;Rog summed it up if you ask me. An ill positioned mob can be fought very close to the HOT (like rog said with their tails sticking out) without aggro'ing any of the mobs outside. If the door opens the +COV mobs will assist the wurms and cause a wipe&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Large models don't have anything to do with aggro range. All mobs have a common center, some slightly larger then others, and that's why you can't sit at the end of a wurms tail and hack at it. So...the wurm's tail sticking through a door/wall would have absolutely no effect on add aggro.<br>
<br>
Another point..ever notice that when a door opens there are usually people nearby who open it? Maybe they aggro the mobs on the otherside? If not then coincidentally dragging a corpse at the same time the door opens doesn't mean you got adds from the door.<br>
<br>
A door is a mere inconvenience to a player. Its only purpose is to keep you from seeing what's on the otherside, a.k.a, Verant's welfare version of a surprise.<br>
<br>
